ie gegenwärtige Migration in die ehemaligen südafrikanischen »Homelands« wird in einen historischen Kontext eingebettet. Durch die Perspektive der Kastenangehörigen gelingt auch der Blick auf die sich wandelnde muslimische Praxis.  aHow do Indo-Muslim migrants practice Islam in South Africa? Through the perspective of caste membership, it is also possible to take a look at dynamic Islamic practices.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 0aEmigration and immigrationxReligious aspectsxIslam. 0aGujaratis (Indic people)zSouth Africa. 0aSunniteszSouth Africa. 4aAfrika. 4aEthnographie. 4aEthnologie. 4aHomelands. 4aIndischer Ozean. 4aMuslime. 4aPost-Apartheid. 4aReligionswissenschaft. 4aSüdafrika. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / Cultural & Social.2bisacsh  aAfrica.  aEthnology.  aHomelands.  aIndian Ocean.  aMuslims.  aPost-apartheid.  aReligious Studies.  aSouth Africa.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2016z978311070100508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2016z9783110485103oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Social Sciences 2016z9783110485332oZDB-23-DSW08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPP Plus eBook-Package 2016z978311070101208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe Gruyterttranscript Complete eBook Package 2014-2016z9783110489842oZDB-23-TGP40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9783839433201zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783839433201423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783839433201/original  a978-3-11-070100-5  DG Plus eBook-Package 2016b2016  a978-3-11-070101-2  PP Plus eBook-Package 2016b2016  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aEBA_STMALL  